  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;enchantment&nbsp;(compulsion)&nbsp;[mind-affecting];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;bard 2, mesmerist 2, psychic 2;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;10 minutes<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M (lemon juice and a scrap of parchment)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;willing creature touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;1 hour/level<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;none;&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>You temporarily alter the target's memory (similar to <i>modify</i> memory) to eliminate, change, or implant a memory of up to 1 hour in length. When the duration of this expires, the target's real memory returns, and the false memory fades to little more than a vague outline, like a dream. This false memory seems true to the target, so effects that detect lies or force the target to speak the truth (as the subject understands it) don't detect the falsehood.</p>\n</div>\n",
